Up to date, various transition-metal oxides (e.g. Fe2O3, Co3O4, and MnO
                        x
                     ) have been widely used as catalyst support for the oxidation of VOCs [14–21]. Among them, Fe2O3 might be more abundant and environmental friendly. Therefore, we herein choose Fe2O3 as the catalyst support, and fabricate the x Pt1/Fe2O3 (x = 0.25 and 0.5 wt%) SACs via a novel and simple impregnation-pyrolysis method for the photothermal catalytic oxidation of toluene. The 0.5 Pt1/Fe2O3 exhibits good light-thermal conversion efficiency and photothermal catalytic activity for toluene oxidation. Furthermore, the possible reaction pathways for the photothermal catalytic oxidation of toluene are proposed.
